Type Casting (primitive data types:

Implicit / widening / automatic type casting
    smaller date type to larger data type
    
Explicit / narrowing / manual type casting  
    larger date type to smaller data type  
    
Why we learn type casting?
    when we write code in our real life most of the time we use the code from other to save 
    time (working on a time continuing someone else work)  convert data type to make our code compatible with their codes

What is syntax type casting

    ()
    long var1=250
    int var2=(int)var1; // explicit / narrowing / manual
    double var3=var2; //  implicit / widening / automatic
======================================================================================= 
if else condition

Syntax
    boolean isHungry=true;
    
    if(isHungry){System.out.println("will buy food')}
    else{ System.out.println("watch a movie")}
    
    
 